\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.2}{\ignorespaces a) False color image of the exfoliated device; numbers denote contacts used. b) $\frac {dI}{dV}$ vs DC Bias voltage for contact 5 at 7 K. c)$\frac {dI}{dV}$ vs DC Bias voltage for contact 3 at 7 K. d) Depiction of contact geometry for top only (5) and hinge (3) contacts. e) Dip number vs. Voltage for c-axis only contacts. The black line is a fit to McMillan-Rowell Oscillations which follow the equation, $\Delta V = n\times \frac {hv_{F}}{4ed_{s}}$. Blue and red points are experimental data extracted from the positive and negative bias voltages respectively. f) Temperature dependence of differential conductance for various temperatures.}}{25}{figure.3.2}%
